 zum sog. Schriftprinzip hat. Eine Bibliographie sämtlicher Publikationen des führenden schwedischen Theologiehistorikers Bengt Hägglund rundet den Band ab.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aGerman literaturexHistory and criticism. 4aBibelhermeneutik. 70(DE-588)4015875-50(DE-627)1044524550(DE-576)208913998aEvangelische Theologie2gnd 70(DE-588)4048946-20(DE-627)1043641650(DE-576)209079851aReformation2gnd 70(DE-588)4128972-90(DE-627)1057132520(DE-576)209606614aHermeneutik2gnd 7aRELIGION / Biblical Studies / Exegesis & Hermeneutics.2bisacsh  aBiblical Hermeneutics (16th and 17th Centuries).1 aAlfsvåg, Knut, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAppold, Kenneth G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArand, Charles P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDanneberg, Lutz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErikson, Leif, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHøjlund, Asger Chr., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohansson, Torbjörn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohansson, Torbjörn, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKoch, Ernst, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKolb, Robert , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKolb, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLund, Eric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMahlmann, Theodor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPaulson, Steven D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSteiger, Johann Ansel